Rivers under strict supervision 
Several courses of a river remain on account of the high precipitation which has poured forth since Tuesday in some regions of the province, furthermore under strict marking. 
It came to Shawinigan, in the administrative region of Mauricie, on the Wednesday afternoon to a landslide. 
Two houses were evacuated preventively. 
In the evening another landslide has occurred in Saint-Lin-Laurentides, in the administrative region of Lanaudiere. 
Besides, a street has collapsed in itself. 
From Tuesday on Wednesday evening strong rainfall of 40 up to 70 milliliters of precipitation on several regions has poured forth. 
Between from 20 to 40 other millimetres of precipitation were expected here according to the regions to Thursday evening. 
The areas to the north of the river as well as the valley of the region of Outaouais were strongest concerned. 
Here had come down all together up to 100 millimetres of shower. 
Because to this precipitation still the thaw is to be included which has already collected in certain branches, violating several watercourses is feared. 
On the Wednesday evening warning tips about the high water alarm were exclaimed by the Quebecer security concerning the rivers Ouareau and Achigan in the region of Lanaudiere. 
The courses of a river in the north, in Saint-Jérôme, in the Laurentinischen to mountains and the Chêne in Lotbinière become here the object of the high water supervision and also remain furthermore under observation. 
In the region of Lanaudière the violent precipitation has passing some lakes in Sainte-Julienne, Sainte-Marcelline-de-Kildare as well as also in Rawdon caused. 
In Saint-Calixte an evasive bridge was torn away on account of the strong rainfall. 
Ten residences had to be evacuated as a preventive measure. 
In Outaouais violating certain lakes has the closing of several streets, caused in particular in the municipality of Mansfield-et-Pontefract. 
The security remains furthermore on the alert and supervises the situation most exactly, according to security council member Annik Bouchard. 
The Quebecer land high water centre has published on his part on Wednesday warning tips of the strong Ansteigens of several rivers, in particular from Maskinongé, Assomption, Ouareau, Achigan, Batiscan and Loup. 
